http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 9 Dec 2011
Source: IBN Live [edited]
http://ibnlive.in.com/generalnewsfeed/news/50-cattle-dead-in-suspected-anthrax/923674.html


50 cattle dead in suspected anthrax
-----------------------------------
More than 50 cattle have died due to suspected anthrax in several
villages of Odisha's tribal-dominated Malkangiri district, official
sources said today [9 Dec 2011]. According to the Malkangiri
veterinary officer in-charge Rajesh Kumar Kuanr cattle deaths of
cattle were reported from about 8 villages under Tandik gram panchayat
in the Korkunda block of the district in the past 5 days.

A veterinary team has reached the affected villages and anti-anthrax
vaccination was undertaken in the entire area to contain the spread of
the disease, he said. Besides, an awareness campaign has been launched
in the area asking villagers not to consume meat of the dead livestock
and instead bury them.

Official sources state that the postmortem of the dead cattle would
reveal the exact cause of their death.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
